vists steeped in Marxist ideology who sought to create a movement that would be both loyal to its socialist principles and appealing to the wider electorate.The Fate of Labour Socialism is a fundamental reexamination of the CCF and Canadian working-class politics in the 1930s, one that will help historians better understand Canada’s political, intellectual, and labour history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aLaborxHistoryx20th centuryxCanada. 0aLaborzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical partiesxHistoryx20th centuryxCanada. 0aPolitical partieszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocialismxHistoryx20th centuryxCanada. 0aSocialismzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorking classxPolitical activityxHistoryx20th centuryxCanada. 0aWorking classxPolitical activityzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066595640uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144262590740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442625907423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442625907.jpg  a978-3-11-066595-6  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles